     <div class = 'birdimg1'>
       <div>
       <span class = "border trans">archaeopteryx</span>
       </div>
      </div>
    <section class = 'section section-dark'>
      
      
      <p>Although birds are mammals, they actually descended from dinosaurs. it has been proven that some dinosaurs had feathers. After the extinction, the reptiles that survived flourished. The one with feathers, over millions of years, evolved into mammals to survive. They also slowly began diversifying. They developed different sizes to survive in different habitats and many sizes of beaks to eat specific foods in their habitats. Today there are over 9000 species of birds.</p>
    </section>

    <section class = 'section section-light'>
      <h1>species of birds</h1>
      <div class = 'birdimg2' >
       <div>
       <span class = "border trans"></span>
       </div>
      </div>
      <p>There are 9000 species of birds. More 1/3 of birds species live and breed in the Americas. All birds are oviparous. One of the most common birds is the Osprey. Ospreys are birds of prey that live in a wide variety of habitats. Other types of birds include ducks, starlings, swifts, partidges, parrots, swans, birds of paradise, etc.</p>
    </section>
