    <section class = 'section section-light'>
      <h1>Birds of Paradise</h1>
      <div class = 'birdimg3' >
       <div>
       <span class = "border trans"></span>
       </div>
      </div>
      <p>Birds of paradise are a group of birds known for their bright plumage. They are mainly found in the forests of eastern Indonesia, Papua New Guinea, and eastern Astralia. Birds of Paradise range in size from 50g and 15cm to 430g and 44cm. The male Black Sicklebill is the longest species of birds of paradise at 110 cm. The body size of a bird of paradise varies with the sex. males are usually larger and longer than females. Some examples of birds of paradise are Magnificent Riflebird, Black Sicklebill, Brown sicklebill, Paradise Riflebird, Magnificent Bird of Paradise, Trumpet Manucode, etc.</p>
